response.overview: GARNiDELiA (ガルニデリア) is a Japanese music group composed of singer MARiA and composer Toku (Abe Naomi). The origin of the group name is "Le Palais Garnier de Maria (French, meaning MARiA's Garnier Opera House)", which is a combination of words from the asteroid 2758 (Cordelia) that was discovered at the same time as Toku's birth year.
